### 4. No CORS Configuration — OWASP A05:2021 Security Misconfiguration

Without explicit CORS policy, browser behavior defaults apply. If CORS middleware is added later without proper configuration, it could allow any origin to access user data.

**Recommendation:**

```js
const cors = require('cors');

app.use(cors({
  origin: ['https://your-trusted-domain.com'],  // explicit allowlist
  methods: ['GET'],
  allowedHeaders: ['Content-Type', 'Authorization'],
}));
```

---

### 5. No Global Error Handling — Information Leakage

If any route throws an unhandled error, Express's default handler will send the **full stack trace** to the client in development mode. This is **OWASP A04:2021 – Insecure Design**.

**Recommendation:** Add an error-handling middleware at the end of the middleware chain:

```js
// Must be the LAST app.use()
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack);  // log internally
  res.status(500).json({
    error: 'Internal server error',
    // NEVER send err.message or err.stack to the client in production
  });
});
```

