Unhandled errors will leak stack traces to clients, revealing internal structure.

```js
// ✅ Fix: add global error handler (must be LAST middleware)
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack); // Log internally
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' }); // Don't leak details
});
```

